d.</p><p>This is achieved by creating an anonymous struct with the same structure as <code>FunctionDefine</code>, but with a new <code>Parameters</code> field. This new field is of type <code>json.RawMessage</code>, which can hold a raw slice of bytes that is included as-is when marshaling to JSON.</p><p>In the call to <code>json.Marshal</code>, the code passes a pointer to a new instance of this anonymous struct. It sets the <code>Alias</code> field to a new <code>Alias</code> (alias of <code>FunctionDefine</code>) instance pointing to <code>fd</code>, and sets the <code>Parameters</code> field to the <code>parameters</code> variable prepared earlier. As a result, the fields of <code>fd</code> (except <code>ParametersRaw</code> and <code>Parameters</code>) are included as-is in the JSON output, and the "parameters" field in the JSON output is sourced from either <code>ParametersRaw</code> or <code>Parameters</code> as appropriate.</p><p>Note: the <code>Alias</code> is used to prevent infinite recursion in the <code>MarshalJSON</code> method.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="h-32 md:h-48 flex-shrink-0"></div></div></div></div><div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-full border-t md:border-t-0 dark:border-white/20 md:border-transparent md:dark:border-transparent md:bg-vert-light-gradient bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 md:!bg-transparent dark:md:bg-vert-dark-gradient pt-2 md:pl-2 md:w-[calc(100%-.5rem)]"><div class="relative flex h-full w-full flex-1 items-center justify-center gap-2"><a as="link" class="btn relative btn-primary" href="https://chat.openai.com/share/bec0bb09-41f5-4746-8b21-8e40087509b1/continue" target="_self" to="https://chat.openai.com/share/bec0bb09-41f5-4746-8b21-8e40087509b1/continue"><div class="flex w-full gap-2 items-center justify-center">Continue this conversation</div></a></div><div class="relative pb-3 pt-2 text-center text-xs text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 md:px-[60px] md:pb-6 md:pt-3"><div class="flex justify-center gap-3 te